1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:13,533
<i>Based on what Selena said,
there's someone here with us.</i>

2
00:00:13,667 --> 00:00:15,067
<i> What I need to know</i>

3
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:17,433
<i>is whether that officer is
indeed Amo's henchman or not.</i>

4
00:00:17,567 --> 00:00:19,267
<i> I'm pissed off with him.</i>

5
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:22,000
<i>Just don't give them any reason
to doubt you.</i>

6
00:00:22,133 --> 00:00:22,867
<i> Befriend him.</i>

7
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:23,800
<i> He likes to drink.</i>

8
00:00:23,933 --> 00:00:25,000
<i> Boss Tonyo!</i>

9
00:00:25,133 --> 00:00:26,633
<i>Your timing is wrong.
What's wrong? I'm working.</i>

10
00:00:26,767 --> 00:00:27,700
<i> You're bothering me!</i>

11
00:00:27,833 --> 00:00:28,967
<i>You know what you're going
to do, right?</i>

12
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:30,200
<i> Just distract them.</i>

13
00:00:30,333 --> 00:00:31,333
<i> Idol!</i>

14
00:00:31,467 --> 00:00:33,067
<i>You're really handsome
in person, aren't you?</i>

15
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,433
<i>You're so annoying, Mister.
Just come back tomorrow.</i>

16
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:37,433
<i>Why did you send them away?
I don't want to waste the vote.</i>

17
00:00:37,567 --> 00:00:39,800
<i>I recognize the guy they were
with earlier.</i>

18
00:00:39,933 --> 00:00:40,667
<i> He's a cop.</i>

19
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:41,733
<i> Are you okay?</i>

20
00:00:41,867 --> 00:00:44,200
<i>I think you're sleeping.
Are you asleep?</i>

21
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:45,133
<i> Where's Tonyo?</i>

22
00:00:45,267 --> 00:00:46,333
<i>Didn't you drink with him
earlier?</i>

23
00:00:46,467 --> 00:00:47,433
<i> He's already wasted.</i>

24
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:48,067
<i> Maybe...</i>

25
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:49,000
<i> Maybe he just peed.</i>

26
00:00:54,367 --> 00:00:55,167
<i> Enriquez?</i>

27
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:57,200
<i>Get me some cash
from the cabinet.</i>

28
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:58,500
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

29
00:00:58,633 --> 00:01:00,433
<i> Quick, quick! Don't go there.</i>

30
00:01:00,567 --> 00:01:01,533
<i> They're going up there.</i>

31
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:07,167
Roman?

32
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:12,967
Roman, there's a car parked
outside the gate earlier.

33
00:01:13,100 --> 00:01:15,167
Can you check it?
I'm getting nervous.

34
00:01:16,733 --> 00:01:17,100
Okay.

35
00:01:17,233 --> 00:01:18,033
Thank you.

36
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:46,867
What are you doing here?

37
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,900
I'm looking for evidence against
Amo.

38
00:01:50,033 --> 00:01:52,333
And you, why do you seem to be
hiding?

39
00:01:52,467 --> 00:01:53,733
Aren't you working here?

40
00:01:53,867 --> 00:01:56,567
I'm also looking for evidence
against him.

41
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:57,767
What?

42
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:58,600
Why?

43
00:01:58,733 --> 00:02:00,133
Aren't you suspended?

44
00:02:00,267 --> 00:02:02,233
Major and I just made that up

45
00:02:03,700 --> 00:02:07,600
because we suspect that Amo
has a henchman in the station.

46
00:02:07,733 --> 00:02:09,467
You and Major just made
this up for a show?

47
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:10,367
Yes.

48
00:02:11,733 --> 00:02:13,000
So go away.

49
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:13,867
Wait a minute.

50
00:02:16,067 --> 00:02:16,967
Hey, hey.

51
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:18,200
What are you doing?

52
00:02:18,333 --> 00:02:20,200
Installing a recording device.

53
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:21,600
Remove that!

54
00:02:21,733 --> 00:02:23,100
I have to do this.

55
00:02:23,233 --> 00:02:24,100
Remove that.

56
00:02:24,233 --> 00:02:26,000
When they see that,
they'll suspect me.

57
00:02:26,133 --> 00:02:27,700
They'll think I'm spying
on them.

58
00:02:27,833 --> 00:02:29,033
Remove that. Come on!

59
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:16,833
Go around the house.

60
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:27,200
Bossing, is there a problem?

61
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:30,633
It seems like our secretary
told you to go back.

62
00:03:30,767 --> 00:03:32,200
Our friend is inside.

63
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:33,300
Ouch!

64
00:03:33,433 --> 00:03:34,533
Friend?

65
00:03:34,667 --> 00:03:35,467
Your friend?

66
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,800
It's Tonyo, Bossing.

67
00:03:36,933 --> 00:03:39,767
He told us that he works
for Amo.

68
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:41,700
We just wanted to visit. But...

69
00:03:43,067 --> 00:03:44,267
no, he's not replying.

70
00:03:45,833 --> 00:03:46,833
Excuse me, Sir.

71
00:03:47,867 --> 00:03:48,733
You're a policeman, right?

72
00:03:48,867 --> 00:03:50,667
Yes, Tonyo is a colleague
of mine.

73
00:03:52,767 --> 00:03:55,000
Tonyo, he's drunk.

74
00:03:55,167 --> 00:03:56,900
He had a drink with me.

75
00:03:57,033 --> 00:03:58,067
Okay, let's do this.

76
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:01,800
I'll tell him that you went
to see him

77
00:04:01,933 --> 00:04:03,333
and you'll be back tomorrow.

78
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:11,367
- How did you get in here?
- Here, here.

79
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:12,867
There?

80
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:13,533
Here.

81
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:29,133
Here.
Here?

82
00:04:30,533 --> 00:04:31,433
You climbed this?

83
00:04:31,567 --> 00:04:32,967
Yes, Sir, there.

84
00:04:34,267 --> 00:04:36,000
That's high. You managed that?

85
00:04:36,133 --> 00:04:37,800
Oh, why, Sir?
Don't you trust me?

86
00:04:37,933 --> 00:04:38,533
You should leave.

87
00:04:38,667 --> 00:04:39,400
Hey!

88
00:04:39,533 --> 00:04:40,067
Sir!

89
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:41,100
- What?
- Just a moment!

90
00:04:42,533 --> 00:04:43,933
I can't climb up there
by myself.

91
00:04:44,067 --> 00:04:45,000
Help me.

92
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:45,800
I thought you said you could
manage.

93
00:04:45,933 --> 00:04:47,267
That's so high.

94
00:04:49,067 --> 00:04:50,700
- Good evening, Mayor.
- Good evening.

95
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:53,233
We're just checking if your
private room is ready.

96
00:04:53,367 --> 00:04:54,100
Thank you.

97
00:04:54,233 --> 00:04:55,000
Thank you.

98
00:04:55,133 --> 00:04:57,467
By the way,
you haven't told me yet.

99
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:00,200
Why was Lieutenant Conde
suspended?

100
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:02,767
That's nothing,
just personal issues.

101
00:05:09,533 --> 00:05:10,267
Mayor.

102
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,933
Lieutenant Garcia, right?

103
00:05:12,067 --> 00:05:13,000
Yes, Sir.

104
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:17,800
You have a date.

105
00:05:19,267 --> 00:05:19,767
Babe.

106
00:05:22,833 --> 00:05:26,033
She's Doc Cecilia.

107
00:05:26,167 --> 00:05:27,400
Hello, Doc.

108
00:05:27,533 --> 00:05:29,100
Good evening, Mayor.

109
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:30,233
Good evening.

110
00:05:31,267 --> 00:05:33,200
Mrs. Guerrero?

111
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:34,833
The one and only.

112
00:05:36,367 --> 00:05:40,333
Lieutenant Garcia,
your girlfriend is beautiful.

113
00:05:40,467 --> 00:05:41,033
Girl...

114
00:05:41,167 --> 00:05:42,400
What's with you?

115
00:05:42,533 --> 00:05:44,233
I haven't answered her yet.

116
00:05:44,367 --> 00:05:45,533
It's embarrassing for the Mayor.

117
00:05:47,033 --> 00:05:48,033
Just kidding.

118
00:05:48,167 --> 00:05:50,867
I mean, I wish you'll have
a tongue of an angel.

119
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:56,933
Why won't she answer you when
you're so kind and so handsome.

120
00:05:58,500 --> 00:06:02,600
Actually, it's rare to have
a gift like yours,

121
00:06:02,733 --> 00:06:05,433
someone who's so honest
and good at reading people.

122
00:06:06,733 --> 00:06:08,000
Okay, we'll go ahead.

123
00:06:08,167 --> 00:06:08,833
Okay.

124
00:06:10,233 --> 00:06:11,533
Doctor Cecilia.

125
00:06:11,667 --> 00:06:12,733
Mayor.

126
00:06:12,867 --> 00:06:15,000
Okay, we'll go ahead.

127
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,800
I thought you could do it?

128
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:31,067
Earlier, that was when I had
to go down.

129
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:33,233
Now, I need to climb up.
How am I going to get up there?

130
00:06:33,367 --> 00:06:34,200
It's high.

131
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:37,267
Okay.

132
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:50,867
Step up here.

133
00:07:03,433 --> 00:07:04,033
Tonyo?

134
00:07:06,167 --> 00:07:07,333
What are you doing there?

135
00:07:34,067 --> 00:07:35,100
What are you doing there?

136
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:41,400
I'm just taking a leak, Father.

137
00:07:42,533 --> 00:07:45,500
I'm already a bit drunk.

138
00:07:45,633 --> 00:07:48,200
There's a CR inside.
Why are you urinating there?

139
00:07:50,467 --> 00:07:54,167
I'm still not familiar inside
and I really can't control it.

140
00:07:56,333 --> 00:07:59,533
Do you have any orders?

141
00:07:59,667 --> 00:08:00,800
No, no, no, nothing.

142
00:08:02,667 --> 00:08:05,167
It looks like you and Roman
are having a good time?

143
00:08:06,833 --> 00:08:11,533
Father, just a little,
just to make us sleepy.

144
00:08:11,667 --> 00:08:18,933
I'm glad you guys are bonding
and getting along.

145
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:23,467
Roman seems like a nice guy.

146
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:28,600
That's good. Come on,
let's drink. Let's go.

147
00:08:39,467 --> 00:08:41,267
Boss, just wait.
My Mother is calling.

148
00:08:44,367 --> 00:08:45,733
Hello, Mom, how are you?

149
00:08:45,867 --> 00:08:47,233
Hello, Noble.

150
00:08:47,367 --> 00:08:49,300
Fetch me where you dropped me
off?

151
00:08:49,433 --> 00:08:51,167
Okay, Mom, we're leaving now.

152
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:52,567
Okay, okay.

153
00:08:54,567 --> 00:08:56,033
Okay, Boss. We're leaving now.

154
00:08:56,167 --> 00:08:57,167
Okay.

155
00:08:58,867 --> 00:08:59,600
Sir, okay.

156
00:09:13,367 --> 00:09:14,333
Boss.

157
00:09:14,467 --> 00:09:15,167
The area is clear.

158
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:16,900
Okay.

159
00:09:17,033 --> 00:09:18,600
Keep an eye on this.

160
00:09:18,733 --> 00:09:20,700
I'm just going to confront
someone.

161
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:25,133
Bobby, let's go!

162
00:09:25,267 --> 00:09:27,100
Hurry, hurry!

163
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:28,133
Open this!

164
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:39,167
Cheers, Father,

165
00:09:40,367 --> 00:09:42,400
for your landslide win.

166
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:46,600
I hope so.

167
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:50,300
What do you mean you hope so?

168
00:09:50,433 --> 00:09:52,467
Don't be like that, Father.

169
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:56,500
- You should think you'll win.
- Tonyo!

170
00:09:58,300 --> 00:09:59,033
Tonyo!

171
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:03,767
What do you have to do
with the police outside?

172
00:10:03,900 --> 00:10:04,767
Nothing!

173
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:06,867
I'm not a policeman now.

174
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,633
Father, he's been drunk
for a while now.

175
00:10:09,767 --> 00:10:12,200
Roman, sit down first.

176
00:10:12,333 --> 00:10:15,333
Amo, the key to the steel
cabinet is missing.

177
00:10:15,467 --> 00:10:18,867
The key I'm holding when we're
just starting to drink,

178
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,467
that you took!

179
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,667
I'm not taking anything
from you!

180
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:25,700
Why would I take that?
We're just drinking here.

181
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:26,800
Where would that go?

182
00:10:26,933 --> 00:10:27,767
Why would I take that?

183
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:29,767
It's just the two
of us drinking here!

184
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:31,700
That's the thing,
we're just drinking.

185
00:10:32,733 --> 00:10:33,867
You're something else!

186
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,333
Admit it!

187
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:37,100
What will I admit?
It's not with me.

188
00:10:37,233 --> 00:10:38,500
You're the only one who'd get
the key...

189
00:10:38,633 --> 00:10:39,633
Is this what you're looking for?

190
00:10:44,300 --> 00:10:45,167
Oh my, Roman.

191
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:48,033
I guess you've been drinking
too much.

192
00:10:48,167 --> 00:10:49,800
You see.

193
00:10:49,933 --> 00:10:52,333
You talk a lot.

194
00:10:52,467 --> 00:10:54,333
You're like a slob!

195
00:10:55,867 --> 00:10:57,000
What did you say?

196
00:10:57,133 --> 00:10:58,533
He is sensitive.

197
00:10:59,567 --> 00:11:02,167
Okay, you're not a slob anymore.

198
00:11:03,667 --> 00:11:06,067
You're just like a plain old
carabao.

199
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:08,300
I'm sorry,

200
00:11:11,767 --> 00:11:12,733
I'm sorry.

201
00:11:16,667 --> 00:11:17,967
Wait, hey!

202
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:19,133
Stop that!

203
00:11:22,833 --> 00:11:25,533
Stop that!
You two should separate.

204
00:11:25,667 --> 00:11:26,967
Oh, that's enough!

205
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:30,033
You're not enemies!

206
00:11:31,733 --> 00:11:33,500
Amo, aren't you surprised?

207
00:11:33,633 --> 00:11:35,833
That scoundrel hasn't cared
about your life for a long time,

208
00:11:35,967 --> 00:11:37,533
and then he suddenly comes here!

209
00:11:37,667 --> 00:11:40,033
Can't I ask my father for help?

210
00:11:40,167 --> 00:11:41,367
I lost my job!

211
00:11:41,533 --> 00:11:42,700
That's enough!

212
00:11:42,833 --> 00:11:44,900
The election is already
my problem,

213
00:11:45,033 --> 00:11:46,267
you're going to add to it!

214
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:01,833
Father, I'm really sorry.

215
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:05,100
That's okay.

216
00:12:06,667 --> 00:12:07,967
Roman is just drunk.

217
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:09,033
Let's go.

218
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,633
Why did we have dinner here?

219
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:18,133
Well, we could just cook
at home if you wanted Leslie

220
00:12:18,267 --> 00:12:20,367
to feel more welcome.

221
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:24,700
I'm courting Leslie
to be vice mayor, remember?

222
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:28,433
And I just want to make
a better impression.

223
00:12:33,300 --> 00:12:35,067
I don't like her.

224
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:36,133
Leslie?

225
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:40,733
No, Lieutenant Garcia's date.

226
00:12:40,867 --> 00:12:42,567
Something's off with her.

227
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:46,567
She's like a villain
in a teleserye.

228
00:12:48,533 --> 00:12:50,200
It's like she has a mistress
vibe.

229
00:12:52,867 --> 00:12:55,667
You know, before I preferred
Boss Amo more,

230
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:59,300
but lately, it seems I'm
getting turn off with him.

231
00:12:59,433 --> 00:13:02,067
I seem to bet on El Hepe more.

232
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:06,600
I like Mayor Guerrero,
but I won't vote for him.

233
00:13:06,733 --> 00:13:07,467
Why?

234
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,033
I don't like his wife.

235
00:13:12,767 --> 00:13:15,500
Mrs. Guerrero is so okay.

236
00:13:15,633 --> 00:13:19,267
That kind of woman is rare,
the one who's so honest.

237
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,600
I don't know.

238
00:13:20,733 --> 00:13:26,333
I just met her earlier,
but I sense bad vibes.

239
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:27,933
You know, you're right.

240
00:13:28,067 --> 00:13:30,900
I feel like she's just insecure
about you.

241
00:13:31,033 --> 00:13:32,700
Why? Because I'm pretty?

242
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:33,867
No.

243
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,033
Because you're dating me.

244
00:13:36,167 --> 00:13:39,100
Did you see how she reacted
to me?

245
00:13:40,133 --> 00:13:41,867
Well, you're blessed.

246
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:42,800
Let's eat?

247
00:13:42,933 --> 00:13:45,000
Anyway, yes, let's order.

248
00:13:50,833 --> 00:13:53,367
This is Vice Mayor Leslie Del
Mundo.

249
00:13:55,633 --> 00:14:00,600
Oh my, looks like something
serious is coming.

250
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:10,267
She's meeting the Mayor?

251
00:14:11,733 --> 00:14:12,367
Waiter.

252
00:14:14,533 --> 00:14:17,733
Okay. Let's go.
Vice, let's go?

253
00:14:21,267 --> 00:14:23,667
You know what, don't you?

254
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:25,300
Please give this to Aguinaldo.

255
00:14:25,433 --> 00:14:26,500
Yes, Sir.

256
00:14:26,633 --> 00:14:28,867
Don't we have anything
to do there, Lieutenant Dizon?

257
00:14:29,033 --> 00:14:31,567
It's a waste of my time hanging
around at your station.

258
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:33,633
What if I just move
to Station 11?

259
00:14:33,767 --> 00:14:36,300
You know, Miss Mira,
this is really how it is here.

260
00:14:36,433 --> 00:14:39,900
There's not much trouble,
so our area is very peaceful.

261
00:14:40,033 --> 00:14:41,900
You know, if you had told
the truth earlier,

262
00:14:42,033 --> 00:14:43,733
we wouldn't be here, Peach.

263
00:14:43,867 --> 00:14:46,567
Chief, where is the women's
desk?

264
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:47,867
What's the problem?

265
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,533
It's my best friend,
she stole my bra!

266
00:14:52,533 --> 00:14:55,933
You're so annoying, Apple!
I didn't steal your bra!

267
00:14:56,067 --> 00:14:57,033
What do you mean no?

268
00:14:57,167 --> 00:14:59,767
Don't lie, Peach! That's mine!
Take it off!

269
00:14:59,900 --> 00:15:01,333
You're so annoying.
You're too much!

270
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:03,200
I didn't steal it!

271
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:04,667
That's mine!

272
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:08,733
Excuse me, I didn't steal it!

273
00:15:08,867 --> 00:15:09,700
What do you mean you didn't
steal it?

274
00:15:09,833 --> 00:15:11,033
Why are you lying?

275
00:15:11,167 --> 00:15:12,700
You can borrow it!

276
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:14,667
Wait a minute, wait a minute,
wait a minute.

277
00:15:16,133 --> 00:15:17,767
You're familiar to me.

278
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:20,367
Aren't you Conde's neighbor?

279
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:22,767
And you're best of friends,
right?

280
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:24,467
Yes, that's right.
We're best friends,

281
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:27,633
but I don't know why she needs
to steal my bra.

282
00:15:27,767 --> 00:15:29,033
You can borrow it!

283
00:15:29,167 --> 00:15:31,133
Excuse me, Apple.
I didn't steal it.

284
00:15:31,267 --> 00:15:32,033
You're annoying!

285
00:15:32,167 --> 00:15:35,633
Don't lie to me. That's mine.

286
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:37,133
You know, Apple.

287
00:15:37,267 --> 00:15:38,633
You're so annoying!

288
00:15:38,767 --> 00:15:40,067
I'm not annoying! It's mine!

289
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:42,300
- Give it to me!
- We have the same color.

290
00:15:42,433 --> 00:15:43,233
It even fits me better. Look!

291
00:15:43,367 --> 00:15:46,667
Wait, wait, wait.

292
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:48,600
Won't you stop?

293
00:15:48,733 --> 00:15:51,133
If you don't stop,
you'll both go to jail.

294
00:15:51,267 --> 00:15:55,467
You, Peach, do you have proof
that that bra is really yours?

295
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:59,300
Yes, I just bought it. I have
a receipt in the dorm, Sir.

296
00:16:01,033 --> 00:16:05,067
You, Apple, do you have proof
that she stole this bra?

297
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:08,600
Yes, I'm sure.
I've lost a few bras already.

298
00:16:08,767 --> 00:16:10,367
We can look in her cabinet.

299
00:16:12,433 --> 00:16:13,400
It seems we have no choice.

300
00:16:13,533 --> 00:16:15,567
It seems we have to go
to your boarding house

301
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:17,900
to solve this case.

302
00:16:18,033 --> 00:16:21,333
- Sir, we'll do it!
- We'll do it, Sir.

303
00:16:21,467 --> 00:16:24,467
Okay, Torres, De Jesus,
you guys...

304
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:25,900
You guys are the ones
who will be left here.

305
00:16:27,067 --> 00:16:28,200
Bautista, come on, come with me.

306
00:16:28,333 --> 00:16:29,033
Yes, Sir.

307
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:32,100
Can I come with you?

308
00:16:32,233 --> 00:16:33,300
Are you sure?

309
00:16:33,433 --> 00:16:35,833
Don't you want to wait
for the next case to come here?

310
00:16:35,967 --> 00:16:38,300
Ah, no. This is actually more
exciting.

311
00:16:38,433 --> 00:16:40,600
I'm already invested
in the bra theft.

312
00:17:06,933 --> 00:17:08,100
How's your date with Dad?

313
00:17:08,233 --> 00:17:09,033
It's good!

314
00:17:09,167 --> 00:17:11,867
He's talking to
Vice Mayor Leslie now,

315
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:15,733
convincing her to be his,
running mate.

316
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:17,833
You should join them.

317
00:17:17,967 --> 00:17:20,667
I just called to tell you

318
00:17:20,800 --> 00:17:26,733
that I saw Cecilia on
a date with a cop.

319
00:17:29,733 --> 00:17:30,200
Wait,

320
00:17:31,667 --> 00:17:33,133
you know about us?

321
00:17:33,267 --> 00:17:34,767
I'm your mother.

322
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:39,033
I know everything,
or so I thought.

323
00:17:39,167 --> 00:17:41,200
Aren't you exclusive?

324
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:43,467
I mean, you let her date
other men?

325
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:46,700
I'll talk to her.

326
00:17:49,267 --> 00:17:50,700
Here's the receipt!

327
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:52,667
I just bought my bra
and panties.

328
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,633
You want my panties, too,
you'll see.

329
00:17:54,767 --> 00:17:55,433
What will I do with that?

330
00:17:55,567 --> 00:17:56,733
Okay, let's see.

331
00:17:56,867 --> 00:17:58,000
The panties, Sir?

332
00:17:58,133 --> 00:17:59,733
The receipt.

333
00:17:59,867 --> 00:18:02,267
This, Sir. That's new.

334
00:18:04,033 --> 00:18:05,967
Yes, that's new.

335
00:18:07,033 --> 00:18:08,667
A pair of red lingerie.

336
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:12,700
When did yours go missing?

337
00:18:12,833 --> 00:18:13,867
Last week.

338
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:17,100
Okay, wait, if not you,
who took my underwear?

339
00:18:17,233 --> 00:18:18,833
Well, Apple, how would I know?

340
00:18:18,967 --> 00:18:21,000
I've been losing some bras
and panties.

341
00:18:21,133 --> 00:18:22,867
Do you want to see my cabinet?

342
00:18:23,033 --> 00:18:24,367
What you're looking
for isn't there.

343
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:27,000
Okay, I'm sorry.

344
00:18:27,133 --> 00:18:28,433
I'm sorry, Bes.

345
00:18:28,567 --> 00:18:31,300
You know my ex gave that to me,

346
00:18:31,433 --> 00:18:33,467
that's why I love that bra
so much.

347
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:35,333
I understand, Bes.

348
00:18:35,467 --> 00:18:37,933
I'm sorry, I got angry too.

349
00:18:38,067 --> 00:18:41,933
Wait, are you missing just your
underwear?

350
00:18:42,067 --> 00:18:43,067
Nothing else?

351
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,567
Yes, that's it.

352
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:48,633
Some of our other dormmates
have lost their underwear.

353
00:18:48,767 --> 00:18:50,267
They said their bras and panties
have gone missing.

354
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:52,233
They're already complaining.

355
00:18:52,367 --> 00:18:54,300
Mr. Mau, what are you doing
there?

356
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:57,400
I just left my rag.

357
00:18:58,533 --> 00:18:59,367
Excuse me.

358
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:12,100
Who's that?

359
00:19:12,233 --> 00:19:13,733
The janitor here.

360
00:19:13,867 --> 00:19:17,267
Are you sure you're missing
just your underwear?

361
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:18,500
Yes.

362
00:19:18,633 --> 00:19:22,733
Because it looks like there was
no forced entry here.

363
00:19:30,233 --> 00:19:31,067
Enriquez,

364
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:34,267
this is what I'm telling you.

365
00:19:36,233 --> 00:19:37,400
Trust the process.

366
00:19:38,967 --> 00:19:41,700
Well, Sir, I wish you had just
laid out the entire process,

367
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:44,333
that you suspended
Lieutenant Conde

368
00:19:44,467 --> 00:19:46,767
so he could get into Amo's
territory.

369
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:48,900
I wish everything were clear.

370
00:19:49,933 --> 00:19:50,700
Enriquez,

371
00:19:53,333 --> 00:19:57,700
Conde and I hid this
because I believe

372
00:19:58,967 --> 00:20:01,133
that Amo has a spy in our ranks.

373
00:20:02,300 --> 00:20:06,533
Chief, Amo has a henchman,
the one who drove us away.

374
00:20:06,667 --> 00:20:08,067
My reading of him isn't good.

375
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:09,333
He seems...

376
00:20:09,467 --> 00:20:10,833
He seems to know a lot.

377
00:20:10,967 --> 00:20:13,800
But he's not Amo's spy here
at the station.

378
00:20:13,933 --> 00:20:15,467
That's why I'm begging you,

379
00:20:16,533 --> 00:20:17,767
whatever you found out,

380
00:20:19,233 --> 00:20:20,567
keep it a secret for now.

381
00:20:20,700 --> 00:20:25,200
Because if too much is known,
Conde will be compromised.

382
00:20:25,333 --> 00:20:26,900
He's not just watching Amo,

383
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:29,800
he's also watching the people
around him.

384
00:20:40,267 --> 00:20:40,933
Wait a minute.

385
00:20:42,133 --> 00:20:43,833
Did you enjoy it?

386
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:45,067
Of course.

387
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:48,400
It's like you didn't.

388
00:20:48,533 --> 00:20:49,767
Did I say anything?

389
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:57,067
Honestly, you know, I think
you're wonderful and funny.

390
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:59,467
The only thing I don't like is

391
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:02,167
that the Mayor paid
for our dinner.

392
00:21:02,300 --> 00:21:04,000
Why would he do that?

393
00:21:04,133 --> 00:21:06,233
What's that?
Are we a charity case?

394
00:21:06,367 --> 00:21:09,033
And besides, we're on a date,

395
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:12,333
so I think he robbed you
of the chance to show me

396
00:21:12,467 --> 00:21:14,267
that you can provide for us,
right?

397
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:15,667
I get it.

398
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:18,100
But wait a minute,
wait a minute?

399
00:21:18,233 --> 00:21:19,000
I'm thrilled.

400
00:21:19,133 --> 00:21:20,733
I'll just go back
to what you said.

401
00:21:20,867 --> 00:21:24,833
Are you still open
to a second date with me,

402
00:21:24,967 --> 00:21:28,900
for me to show you that I can
provide for us?

403
00:21:29,033 --> 00:21:29,667
Of course.

404
00:21:32,767 --> 00:21:36,767
Okay. Next time, let's go to
Aling Issy's food stall.

405
00:21:36,900 --> 00:21:37,933
Anywhere!

406
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:47,133
I won't kiss you,
but if you want, I can.

407
00:21:47,267 --> 00:21:50,867
No, two people are watching us
from afar.

408
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,433
They're a bit suspicious.

409
00:21:52,567 --> 00:21:53,400
Behind us.

410
00:21:53,533 --> 00:21:55,000
Don't look at them.

411
00:21:55,133 --> 00:21:57,033
Let's just pretend to be happy.

412
00:21:57,167 --> 00:21:58,900
Hold my left cheek.

413
00:21:59,033 --> 00:21:59,633
Come on!

414
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:03,700
What's with you? Not here.
There are so many people here.

415
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:04,767
Let's go there.

416
00:22:06,433 --> 00:22:07,967
It's really fun, isn't it?

417
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:23,733
Mister, Mau, right?

418
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:26,467
Yes, Ma'am.

419
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:27,700
You have a lot of keys?

420
00:22:30,967 --> 00:22:33,133
I'm a janitor and maintenance
guy here.

421
00:22:33,267 --> 00:22:36,300
Change the light,
fix the broken pipe, all around.

422
00:22:36,433 --> 00:22:40,533
So that means you have access
to all the rooms here?

423
00:22:40,667 --> 00:22:41,167
What?

424
00:22:42,267 --> 00:22:43,900
I'm not a thief, Ma'am.

425
00:22:44,033 --> 00:22:45,933
Even if you ask the boarders.

426
00:22:46,067 --> 00:22:48,800
No one is stealing money
or jewelry here.

427
00:22:48,967 --> 00:22:51,000
I'm not saying you're a thief,

428
00:22:51,133 --> 00:22:53,333
but I still need to see
the stockroom.

429
00:22:55,767 --> 00:22:56,233
Wait.

430
00:22:56,367 --> 00:22:57,033
Sir...

431
00:22:57,167 --> 00:22:57,733
Where are you going?

432
00:22:57,867 --> 00:22:59,267
Sir, I'm not a thief, Sir.

433
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:01,533
Ma'am...

434
00:23:01,667 --> 00:23:04,800
Okay, let's say you're not
stealing anything,

435
00:23:04,933 --> 00:23:07,733
but we need to see what's inside
the stockroom.

436
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:12,033
Where are they?

437
00:23:12,167 --> 00:23:13,233
They disappeared so quickly.

438
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:16,200
They were just here earlier.

439
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:18,100
What?

440
00:23:18,233 --> 00:23:19,300
Have you seen it?

441
00:23:19,433 --> 00:23:20,133
No, we didn't.

442
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,433
You're robbers, right?

443
00:23:23,567 --> 00:23:25,033
Well, what if I rob you?

444
00:23:25,167 --> 00:23:26,667
I don't have the money
to pay for a date.

445
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:27,333
What?

446
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:34,100
Your turn.

447
00:23:36,133 --> 00:23:37,167
I'm not left-handed.

448
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,567
You're strong,
but you're slow!

449
00:23:45,933 --> 00:23:46,633
I told you...

450
00:24:05,300 --> 00:24:08,233
Don't! Let's go! Let's go!

451
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:10,767
Eric!

452
00:24:11,933 --> 00:24:13,867
Let me. I'll take care of you!

453
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:16,433
What?

454
00:24:17,467 --> 00:24:18,367
Are you okay?

455
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:19,133
I'm okay.

456
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:21,367
What?

457
00:24:24,767 --> 00:24:27,600
If you're not a thief,
what does this mean?

458
00:24:31,567 --> 00:24:33,033
Is this what you're looking for?

459
00:24:37,233 --> 00:24:38,567
This is my bra!

460
00:24:38,700 --> 00:24:40,567
Wait, these are my panties too!

461
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:43,033
Mau, are you the one who stole
our panties and bra?

462
00:24:43,167 --> 00:24:44,600
- You're a maniac! You animal!
- I'm sorry, Ma'am.

463
00:24:44,733 --> 00:24:45,667
Are you the thief?

464
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:48,667
- No! I'm sorry!
- Wait, wait! That's enough!

465
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:51,100
- You're crazy, Mau.
- That's enough.

466
00:24:51,233 --> 00:24:53,233
Who stole the panties and bra!

467
00:24:53,367 --> 00:24:53,933
Was it you, Mau?

468
00:24:54,067 --> 00:24:54,900
Mother...

469
00:24:55,033 --> 00:24:55,933
Mother, forgive me!

470
00:24:56,067 --> 00:25:03,967
- Wait! Miss.that's enough.
- You're crazy!

471
00:25:04,133 --> 00:25:07,167
That's enough.
We'll take you to the precinct.

472
00:25:07,300 --> 00:25:12,667
- You're crazy!
- Go ahead.

473
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:14,733
Mau is a thief.

474
00:25:16,800 --> 00:25:17,933
Bes, sorry.

475
00:25:18,067 --> 00:25:20,367
I've accused you.

476
00:25:20,500 --> 00:25:22,633
It's okay, I understand, Bes.

477
00:25:22,767 --> 00:25:24,067
Me too, I lost some items too.

478
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:25,500
It's good we found out
who did it.

479
00:25:27,133 --> 00:25:28,800
We should go straight
to the hospital.

480
00:25:28,933 --> 00:25:30,967
I'm not going to the hospital.
That's just a weakling.

481
00:25:31,100 --> 00:25:32,467
What happened to your face?

482
00:25:33,867 --> 00:25:37,533
Well, I got into a fight
with the robbers.

483
00:25:37,700 --> 00:25:39,600
But I still managed.

484
00:25:40,900 --> 00:25:42,933
Did you lose anything, Sir?

485
00:25:43,067 --> 00:25:44,300
Nothing.

486
00:25:44,433 --> 00:25:46,367
You know this is just my hobby.

487
00:25:46,500 --> 00:25:47,500
I'm used to fighting.

488
00:25:47,633 --> 00:25:49,000
I went into a brawl to sweat.

489
00:25:49,133 --> 00:25:51,333
Sir, did you recognize
the robbers?

490
00:25:51,467 --> 00:25:52,167
No.

491
00:25:53,233 --> 00:25:55,933
Sir, isn't this a targeted
attack?

492
00:25:56,067 --> 00:25:58,033
Do you have enemies?

493
00:25:59,367 --> 00:26:02,167
Or maybe it's one of the cases
you're handling.

494
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:04,300
Not really.

495
00:26:06,533 --> 00:26:09,333
Eric, I'll just go
to the washroom?

496
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:10,433
I'll be back.

497
00:26:10,567 --> 00:26:11,400
Oh, okay.

498
00:26:15,333 --> 00:26:16,500
Is she gone?

499
00:26:16,633 --> 00:26:21,167
It hurts, it hurts, okay.
Get me some paracetamol.

500
00:26:21,300 --> 00:26:22,300
Three, three.

501
00:26:22,433 --> 00:26:23,167
It hurts.

502
00:26:24,633 --> 00:26:26,567
It felt like my skull
was shaken.

503
00:26:26,700 --> 00:26:28,933
I was going to have
a hemorrhage.

504
00:26:29,067 --> 00:26:32,800
It's a good thing that Ces
wasn't hurt by that goon.

505
00:26:32,933 --> 00:26:36,967
He was about to attack her,
but his companion stopped him.

506
00:26:37,100 --> 00:26:38,733
I have a feeling he was scared
of me.

507
00:26:43,133 --> 00:26:44,500
What's taking the paracetamol
too long?

508
00:26:46,267 --> 00:26:47,367
Sir, just a moment?

509
00:26:49,133 --> 00:26:51,100
Look what you've gotten yourself
into.

510
00:26:55,100 --> 00:26:56,067
What?

511
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:57,133
Everything is planned out?

512
00:26:59,267 --> 00:27:01,600
Tomorrow, Vice Mayor Del Mundo
will announce

513
00:27:01,733 --> 00:27:04,000
that she will be supporting
Dad as Mayor.

514
00:27:05,600 --> 00:27:07,100
You know what to do.

515
00:27:07,233 --> 00:27:08,133
I'll take care of it.

516
00:27:10,167 --> 00:27:11,600
I'll plant it tomorrow too.

517
00:27:11,733 --> 00:27:13,433
I have an IED supplier.

518
00:27:31,567 --> 00:27:34,667
I need your help
to warn the people

519
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:36,267
that there's a bomb inside.

520
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:37,667
- Bomb?
- Bomb?

521
00:27:37,800 --> 00:27:38,900
Is Sir Tonyo sure?

522
00:27:39,033 --> 00:27:41,800
I don't know, but we need to get
those people out of there,

523
00:27:41,933 --> 00:27:43,400
whether there's a bomb or not.
Let's go!

524
00:27:43,533 --> 00:27:45,133
We're arresting you

525
00:27:45,267 --> 00:27:49,767
for violating Presidential
Decree 1727.

526
00:27:49,933 --> 00:27:50,533
What's that?

527
00:27:50,667 --> 00:27:51,600
Bomb jokes are not allowed.

528
00:27:51,733 --> 00:27:53,467
What if what they're saying
is true?

529
00:27:53,600 --> 00:27:55,967
Shouldn't you stop the program
for everyone's safety?

530
00:27:56,100 --> 00:27:58,767
Amo, what's wrong
with Del Mundo?

531
00:27:58,900 --> 00:28:02,067
She should have said she was
going to the other side, right?

532
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:03,833
It would be nice
to blow them up, right?

533
00:28:03,967 --> 00:28:04,633
Hello?

534
00:28:04,767 --> 00:28:05,667
What's the update?

535
00:28:05,800 --> 00:28:06,900
It's okay, Boss.
It's already positioned...

536
00:28:07,033 --> 00:28:08,600
There's a flower in the middle
of the stage.

537
00:28:08,733 --> 00:28:10,467
Sir, I'm begging you.
There's a bomb.

538
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:11,733
Those people and the Mayor
are in danger.

539
00:28:11,867 --> 00:28:13,100
We need to evacuate them now.
